lects that dynamic, combining first-person narrative, dialogue, and the polyphony of Roy's bandmates' voices. Listening to recordings and looking at old photographs elicited more recollections, which allowed Roy to expand on recurring themes and motifs. This congenial, candid book offers different ways of knowing Roy's labor of love-his sound and work through sound, his reputation and circulation as a renowned musician and bandleader in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aBand musicianszTrinidad and TobagovBiography. 0aCalypso musicianszTrinidad and TobagovBiography. 0aSaxophonistszTrinidad and TobagovBiography. 7aMUSIC / Individual Composer & Musician.2bisacsh1 aCape, Roy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822376163zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822376163423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822376163.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles